cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with developing machine learning models to estimate perceived quality in audiovisual multimedia services. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves using network parameters and packet headers, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of machine learning methods also indicates that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the models, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper also involves analyzing audiovisual content, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
